The Operating System Function File Management keeps a track of all the files in the drive; their location, information, and status. The File Management Function also decides which files will get resources and be pulled first.
This collective is known as File System.
The File Management Function also decides which files will get resources and be pulled first.
Another function of the OS is Processor Management
In a multi-programming environment, it is OS who decides which process will get the processor when and for how long.
This task is called Process Scheduling.
